!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

united /juːˈnaɪtɪd/

1. ADJ When people are united about something, they agree about it and act together. 团结的 

例： The entire Brazilian people are united by their love of football. 整个巴西民族由其对足球的热爱团结在一起。 

2. ADJ United is used to describe a country which has been formed from two or more states or countries. 联盟的 

例： ...the first elections to be held in a united Germany for fifty eight years. …在统一的德国将举行58年来的第一次竞选。

</div>

